4 HJR___ RECOGNIZING THE 43RD ALABAMA STATE GAMES OPENING
5 CEREMONY AS IT HONORS THE 250TH BIRTHDAY OF THE UNITED
6 STATES OF AMERICA AND HONORS ALABAMA HEROES AND THEIR
7 DESCENDANTS.
8
9 WHEREAS, it is with the highest commendation and
10 esteem that the Alabama Legislature recognizes the 43rd
11 Alabama State Games Opening Ceremony as an America 250
12 Alabama-certified event; and
13 WHEREAS, the Alabama State Games, originally known as
14 the Alabama Sports Festival (ASF), operating as a 501(c)(3)
15 nonprofit organization, was established at the request of
16 the United States Olympic Committee and incorporated in
17 1982; it is a member of the National Congress of State Games
18 and the second-oldest State Games program in the United
19 States; and
20 WHEREAS, the Alabama State Games touches the lives of
21 thousands of Alabamians each year by creating an
22 Olympic-style experience, encouraging academic achievement
23 by awarding, to date, 660 academic scholarships totaling
24 $466,000 to participating athletes, and hosting additional
25 programs to encourage academics, healthy lifestyles, and
26 good citizenship; and
27 WHEREAS, 2026 is the Semiquincentennial Anniversary
28 of the signing of the Declaration of Independence, a
Page 1

of the signing of the Declaration of Independence, a
HJR99 INTRODUCED
29 revolutionary statement of sovereignty for the 13 American
30 colonies from the rule of England, which launched the United
31 States as a new nation; and
32 WHEREAS, Alabama was admitted to the Union as the
33 22nd state on December 14, 1819; and
34 WHEREAS, the ASF Foundation, in keeping with the
35 teaching of positive values to the youth of Alabama, has
36 chosen the Opening Ceremony of the 43rd Alabama State Games,
37 to be held on Friday, June 12, 2026, inside Legacy Arena at
38 the Birmingham–Jefferson Convention Center, as the platform
39 to honor the 250th birthday of the United States of America
40 with a patriotic ceremony directed by the staff of Troy
41 University's John M. Long School of Music, featuring
42 performances by musical artists Deborah Allen, Savanna Kirby
43 and POPulus, Troy University's prestigious music ensemble,
44 and televised statewide on Gray Media–owned television
45 stations; and
46 WHEREAS, the ASF Foundation was created in 2001
47 following the tragic September 11th attacks on New York and
48 Washington, D.C., and its program, Honoring Our Heroes,
49 recognizes individuals in our communities who sacrifice to
50 keep our neighborhoods safe and healthy; and
51 WHEREAS, because we are celebrating 250 years of
52 America and the peace, freedoms, and prosperity it has
53 offered, the Alabama State Games finds it fitting and proper
54 to recognize, with a commemorative medal, the immense
55 historical significance and continued contributions
56 individuals have made and continue to make to the security
Page 2

individuals have made and continue to make to the security
HJR99 INTRODUCED
57 and prosperity of the State of Alabama and the nation as a
58 whole; and
59 WHEREAS, on June 12, 2026, the ASF Foundation will
60 add to the Honoring Our Heroes legacy by celebrating those
61 Alabamians and their families who have positively
62 contributed to the United States, including Native Americans
63 and descendants of Native Americans; active-duty and retired
64 military members and their descendants; descendants of
65 individuals who have served in any military capacity since
66 the American Revolutionary War; and descendants of
67 individuals who have contributed to the socio-economic
68 welfare of Alabama culturally and historically since its
69 founding, including contributions in science, music,
70 literature, civic service, business, finance, and sports;
71 now therefore,
72 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
73 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That on behalf of the State of
74 Alabama and the citizens thereof, we hereby recognize the
75 efforts of the Alabama State Games and join together in
76 united support in celebrating the 250th Birthday of the
77 United States of America and in honoring all those who have
78 directly or indirectly contributed to this great nation
79 throughout its 250 years.
80 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That the Legislature of
81 Alabama encourages city and county governments, Alabama
82 veterans' and military organizations, individuals,
83 companies, corporations, and community organizations to join
84 with the Alabama State Games and the State of Alabama in
Page 3

with the Alabama State Games and the State of Alabama in
